snippet.textDisplay:
I enjoyed these commentator more then the real life race commentators. Plenty of details about what is going on. And the camera coverage blows away the real world coverage. Obviously a game would have an advantage on the angles it can capture but perhaps in the future a computer program can run the coverage in a similar way in real world racing.
I would imagine if you provided the data of track position of every car to a program such as the one used in this game you would have similar coverage.

snippet.textDisplay: Giovinazzi also did a very good and also very smart race. When Leclerc challenged him with DRS he, unlike all the other drivers, didn't fight him, because his pace was clearly faster. By that he didnt lose any more time onto the drivers behind him. By then just steadily driving without an error he got the overtake back onto Leclerc who had an error. He defends in the last few rounds against Deletraz, who gets onto the curb and has an error as well. Sadly Leclerc closes the gap again and overtakes him so he finishes P5, but still very good drive.

snippet.textDisplay: Stop putting in celebrity non-driver wildcards.  It doesn't add anything and only the risk that some pleb ruins a race for others.  Stop treating esports like a gimmick; we just want to see some good racing.  Current drivers, ex-drivers, drivers of other formulas, competent streamers - great.  But Olympians, cricketers, chefs and singers should have no place here. It's just a clunky grab at publicity - which is crazy considering how many 'stars' you already have in the driver field.
